CSS Rules

CSS consist of 3 elements:
1.Selector
2.Property
3.Value

E.g
body {
    color: pink: 
}

Selector -> body
Property -> color
Value -> pink


Selector 
Definition: determines which HTML element to apply the CSS
Types:
Type Selector: refers to elements with a specific HTML
Class Selector: refers to elements of a particular Class and begin with .
ID Selector: refers to elemets with an attribute ID and begin with #


Property
Various kinds but color, background-color and font are the famous ones


Value
Are hex or rgb values as well as font sizes

